data.value:
Standard MGE usage setup guide:
Graphics and shader setup
1. Select resolution. Click auto-FOV if you prefer FOV adjustment for widescreen. 2. Use some anisotropic filtering, at least 4x. Select fog mode "Range vertex". 3. Set up your shader chain by clicking [Shader setup], then following the notes there.
Distant land setup
1. Run the Distant Land generator wizard. 2. Click the use current load order button, then continue. 3. Click the run automatically button. 4. Wait a long time. 5. Check the status bar for possible errors.
In-game setup
1. The macro editor lets you bind keys to MGE functions. It's recommended to bind "toggle shaders", so you can turn them off if the fps hit is too much. 2. Turn off "responsive menu caching" if you have SLI or Crossfire, they cause slowdown with this feature. 3. Set up third person camera position if you wish to use it.
You should now be set up to play.
